1695
01:54:03,400 --> 01:54:06,700
Suppose we drive into town
and you all be my guests at a nightclub.

1696
01:54:06,600 --> 01:54:08,700
- What do you say?
- Nightclub now?

1697
01:54:08,700 --> 01:54:11,600
Yes. We could see an early floor show,
and I can catch my plane.

1698
01:54:11,600 --> 01:54:13,700
- No, let's not.
- Why?

1699
01:54:14,400 --> 01:54:17,400
Well, I haven't been
in one of those spots in years.

1700
01:54:17,300 --> 01:54:21,100
We're just country folks, Tom.
We don't go for that fast life.

1701
01:54:21,100 --> 01:54:24,700
Anyway, Mama and Papa
wouldn't be interested in a nightclub.

1702
01:54:24,600 --> 01:54:25,800
Yes, we would.

1703
01:54:26,800 --> 01:54:28,500
There you are.

1704
01:54:28,500 --> 01:54:32,600
And it's not your anniversary, son,
it's theirs. Come on, let's go.

1705
01:55:13,100 --> 01:55:18,000
In all your years in show business, Papa,
you didn't see anything like this yet.

1706
01:55:32,800 --> 01:55:36,500
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, I'm interrupting</i>
<i>the show to make an announcement.</i>

1707
01:55:36,300 --> 01:55:37,900
<i>We have a celebrity with us...</i>

1708
01:55:38,000 --> 01:55:40,500
<i>a man you've enjoyed and admired</i>
<i>for many years.</i>

1709
01:55:40,400 --> 01:55:43,200
<i>He's been away for a long time,</i>
<i>and we've missed him a lot.</i>

1710
01:55:43,200 --> 01:55:45,600
<i>But he still is the greatest entertainer</i>
<i>of them all.</i>

1711
01:55:45,600 --> 01:55:47,000
Wonder who he means?

1712
01:55:46,900 --> 01:55:48,900
<i>It's an honor to introduce...</i>

1713
01:55:56,500 --> 01:55:59,500
<i>That's right, it's</i> Mammy
<i>and the man who made it famous...</i>

1714
01:55:59,500 --> 01:56:01,400
<i>the one and only Al Jolson!</i>

1715
01:56:13,700 --> 01:56:14,700
The idiot.

1716
01:56:14,700 --> 01:56:17,100
<i>There's a slight chance,</i>
<i>if we ask him hard enough...</i>

1717
01:56:17,000 --> 01:56:20,500
<i>just for old times' sake,</i>
<i>Mr. Jolson might give us a song.</i>

1718
01:56:20,700 --> 01:56:23,300
- This guy's crazy.
- Come on, Al!

1719
01:56:26,700 --> 01:56:28,300
Sorry, no.

1720
01:56:31,600 --> 01:56:35,400
They're not going to stop.
Better do it and get it over with.

1721
01:56:37,200 --> 01:56:41,200
Baby, it looks like
I'm not going to get out of this. I'm sorry.

1722
01:56:54,900 --> 01:56:58,700
Thanks, Eddie. Thank you, boys.
That was a big introduction.

1723
01:56:58,700 --> 01:57:00,500
Just talk into this?

1724
01:57:01,400 --> 01:57:04,300
<i>Thank you, folks.</i>
<i>It's nice to be remembered.</i>

1725
01:57:04,600 --> 01:57:06,200
<i>I can't tell you how nice.</i>

1726
01:57:06,200 --> 01:57:09,800
<i>But about singing for you,</i>
<i>you see, I'm a little rusty...</i>

1727
01:57:10,100 --> 01:57:12,600
<i>but you asked for it,</i>
<i>so we'll just make it a quick one.</i>

1728
01:57:12,600 --> 01:57:15,900
- What do the boys handle that I can sing?
- Anything.

